org.jcatapult.struts.fileupload
Class FileUploadInfo

java.lang.Object
  org.jcatapult.struts.fileupload.FileUploadInfo

public class FileUploadInfo
extends Object

This class stores the file upload information that Struts adds to the stack in a nice encapsulated form.

Method Detail

getFile

public File getFile()
Returns:
The File that was uploaded and stored on disk by Struts.

setFile

public void setFile(File file)
Set by Struts to the location on disk of the file that was uploaded. This name will most likely be a UUID of sorts and not usable in general. Most applications will move the file to something specific or to the name given via the getName() method that is setup by Struts.

Parameters:
file - The file.

getName

public String getName()
Returns:
The name of the file that was specified by the user via the browser or some other HTTP interface.

setName

public void setName(String name)
Set by Struts to the name of the file that the user selected in their browser or via some other HTTP interface.

Parameters:
name - The name of the file.

getContentType

public String getContentType()
Returns:
The content type of the file as it was determined by browser and specified in the HTTP multipart request header.

setContentType

public void setContentType(String contentType)
Set by Struts to the content type that was sent from the browser or other HTTP interface.

Parameters:
contentType - The content type of the file uploaded.
